 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vairus>Vairus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/01 6:09:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re: getting a high level to weaken, and then a lower level..</span><hr size=1> For the people saying this is a no rules server, it's time to stop hiding behind that one.  There are rules, they are just different from rules on other servers, and maybe there are less of them.  The no rules diatribe is not a valid argument.<br>
<br>
That being said, if you're here, understand what the rules are and base your perception of the server on them.  I don't like them all, but I accept them, it's part of being on this server.<br>
<br>
THAT being said, I do have a couple of ideas to solve these types of problems:<br>
<br>
1) Remove the experience loss from direct pvp.  It would alleviate this problem (and remove one potential lure from lowbie farming), and also encourage more pvp in general, which I thought is what this server is about.  It's called the Deity War Server, not the experience loss due to pvp server.  Why they felt compelled to put experience loss in in the first place baffles me.  There's already enough potential difficulty in dying anyway.<br>
<br>
2) Lose the stupid point system.  It shows nothing about who is winning the Deity War, it only shows who has figured out the easiest way to collect points.  Lose the point system, and you remove another reward to those who enjoy being on the lopsided end of lopsided battles.  If you want to wax lowbies because it's fun for you or you think it will benefit your team, go right ahead.  But why we should keep track of these little episodes of lameness also baffles me.  Once again, it's called the Deity War server, not the point gathering server.  If anything they should put the point system on Rallos which is more individual oriented, or just open up a new point gathering server.  Remember that the points system was an afterthought also.  I find it sad that Verant can't just let the server develop without trying to foist some hacknied quantitative way of &quot;measuring&quot; what is going on.  Do you really need points to tell you that Neutral is winning?  Isn't it enough to know that they own Vellious?  Points - blech - it's just a way to amuse children who can't think abstractly, or comprehend what's going on around them.<br>
<br>
Let me emphasize, I accept the way the server is, and I'll continue to operate under the structure provided.  These were just a couple of experiments Verant has tried here which I don't think have panned out, let's put them to bed, and in so doing solve some problems other people seem to be having. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/umatrimsz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MatrimSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Regular</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/01 6:10:50 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/SoHo/Gallery/4260/t-balsam1.gif width=60 height=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting a high level to weaken, and then a lower level k</span><hr size=1> Thanks for your mildly retarded flames Arcanist and...whoever the hell else was that flamed me.  Sorry, you're not important enough for me to remember your name.<br>
